<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; CENTENNIAL FARM DOCENTS NEEDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Docents are needed to conduct educational tours of the Centennial Farm at the 
Orange County Fairgrounds in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 This miniature working farm is designed to give local schoolchildren hands-on 
experiences tending crops and caring for farm animals. 
</P>
<P>
 Training sessions will be held for new docents, who do not need a background 
in agriculture. Volunteers will lead the tours from 9 to 11 a.m. Tuesdays 
through Fridays from Oct. 4 to May 26. 
</P>
<P>
 Since 1989, more than 125,000 schoolchildren have visited the one-acre farm, 
which is planted with beans, beets, corn, watermelon and other crops. Farm 
animals include horses, sheep, pigs, goats and chickens. 
</P>
<P>
 Persons interested in being docents may call Ginny Smith at (714) 708-1517. 
School field trips can be arranged by calling JoAnn Robinson at (714) 
708-1566.ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
