<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COSTA MESA; 3-DAY HOT-ROD SHOW AT FAIRGROUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM RAGAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Move over Mercedes-Benz and BMW. Make way for the 1940 Fords and '57 Chevys. 
</P>
<P>
 For those who love old cars and 1950s tunes, the Orange County Cruisin' Assn. 
is having its 12th annual hot-rod show this weekend at the Orange County 
Fairgrounds. 
</P>
<P>
 The three-day car show, which runs from 9 a.m. to 10 p.m. Saturday and Sunday, 
will feature an estimated 1,200 cars, including old Model A's and T-buckets.  
</P>
<P>
 No cars built after 1969 will be entered. 
</P>
<P>
 "There will be lots of nice cars with lots of nice people," said Jeff White, a 
board member of the association. 
</P>
<P>
 There will also be a '50s costume contest and two bands performing music from 
the same era: "Captain Cardiac and the Coronaries" and "Li'l Elmo and the 
Cosmos." 
</P>
<P>
 Arts and crafts shows, model car contests and wild wagon competitions will 
also be held on the fairgrounds, where an estimated 15,000 people are expected, 
White said. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are $7.50 for ages 12 and older.TOM RAGAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
