</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Animal Rescue Foundation will hold its second annual "Elegant Silent 
Auction" Sept. 11. 
</P>
<P>
 Some of the items to be auctioned off include animal-themed art by William 
Wegman, Suzanne Somers memorabilia, resort vacations and restaurant gift 
certificates. The auction will be from 4 to 5:30 p.m. at the Cafe Mozart, 31952 
Camino Capistrano. 
</P>
<P>
 Admission is $15 and champagne and hors d'oeuvres will be served. 
</P>
<P>
 ARF, which has 1,500 members, offers wildlife rescues, a meals-on-wheels pet 
food program, classes in responsible pet ownership and an adoption service for 
homeless animals. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information on the auction, call (714) 496-4909. LYNN FRANEY 
