ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; COLLEGE OFFERING NON-CREDIT COURSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saddleback College's community education department is offering more than 200 
non-credit courses for the fall semester. 
</P>
<P>
 The department's non-credit courses cover a range of topics, such as personal 
finance, popular computer software and even horse psychology -- one of the 
offerings among a new series on equestrian pursuits. 
</P>
<P>
 Courses are also available for those who want to prepare for the Scholastic 
Aptitude Test. 
</P>
<P>
 Registering for community education classes can be done by telephone using a 
credit card, by mail or in person. 
</P>
<P>
 The college's community education department is on the campus in the 
Administration and Governance Building. The college is at 28000 Marguerite 
Parkway. 
</P>
<P>
 Class schedules were mailed out last week.  
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 582-4646.JEFF BEAN 
