</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CARLOS V. LOZANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County's top law enforcement officers have endorsed Simi Valley 
Councilwoman Judy Mikels for county supervisor. 
</P>
<P>
 Dist. Atty. Michael D. Bradbury, Sheriff Larry Carpenter and representatives 
of the Deputy Sheriff's Assn. formally announced their endorsements of Mikels' 
candidacy at a news conference Tuesday at the County Government Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Mikels is running against Moorpark City Councilman Scott Montgomery for the 
seat being vacated by Supervisor Vicky Howard. The 4th District supervisorial 
seat represents Simi Valley, Moorpark and the Santa Rosa Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 "Judy Mikels has substantial experience in government and business, is well 
known for her strong support of law enforcement and, most importantly, is a 
person of integrity," Bradbury said of his decision to back Mikels. "When she 
makes a commitment to the people of this county, we can rest assured she will 
keep it." 
</P>
<P>
 Mikels welcomed the support, which she said will provide a big boost to her 
campaign. 
</P>
<P>
 "They don't give their endorsement lightly," Mikels said, "and I don't take it 
lightly." CARLOS V. LOZANO 
</P>
