By MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura County Board of Supervisors on Tuesday approved AIDS education 
contracts for two agencies, focusing on Latinas of childbearing age and young 
gay men. 
</P>
<P>
 El Concilio Del Condado De Ventura, a local Latino organization, was granted 
$31,900 to provide AIDS education services to the Latino community, focusing on 
young women.Robert Collins, an AIDS educator at the Gay and Lesbian Community 
Center, was awarded $41,000 to provide AIDS prevention services to gay and 
bisexual men, primarily those who are young. 
</P>
<P>
 Both contracts are part of a master funding plan for state-supported AIDS 
education, testing and case management approved by the board last week. 
</P>
