<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COOUNTY FOCUS: OAK VIEW; 3 HELD IN CONNECTION WITH STREET BRAWL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Oak View men and a juvenile were in custody Tuesday in connection with a 
brawl between them and youths who had been playing football in an Oak View 
street. 
</P>
<P>
 Nathan Terrazas and Vincent Dealba, both 18, were arrested on suspicion of 
assault with a deadly weapon, Ventura County Sheriff's Detective Maureen 
Hookstra said. 
</P>
<P>
 Bail for each was $5,000, and their arraignment was scheduled today, Sgt. 
Bruce Macedo said. 
</P>
<P>
 The third suspect, a 17-year-old, was taken to Ventura County Juvenile Hall, 
Hookstra said. 
</P>
<P>
 Hookstra said the incident began about 4:50 p.m. Monday when the three, who 
were in a vehicle, confronted five youths who were playing football on Bundren 
Street. 
</P>
<P>
 One of the players, 18-year-old Michael York of Oak View, was struck in the 
head by a flashlight during the ensuing scuffle, Hookstra said. 
</P>
<P>
 She said deputies, who were called by a neighbor, apprehended the three 
suspects a short time later in Ojai. 
</P>
<P>
 York, who lives on Bundren Street, declined to be treated at the scene, she 
added. GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
