<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: THEY ARE INDEED BITING, BUT ONLY AT RIGHT SPOTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Trout, catfish or largemouth bass -- take your pick for the last big 
freshwater fishing weekend of the year. 
</P>
<P>
 All should be available at various sites throughout Southern California and 
the Eastern Sierra, but anglers will have to decide what they want because only 
one species is biting at a given spot. 
</P>
<P>
 For those who can take the heat, Irvine Lake and Corona Lake have been loaded 
with catfish. Eastern Sierra lakes will receive special plants of oversize 
Alpers trout. 
</P>
</TEXT>
