<P>
 With a strong offensive line led by first-team all-league selection Fewel at 
guard and a good running back in Montgomery, Turek believes the Warriors have a 
good chance to repeat their league-winning performance of last year. And though 
he acknowledges his defensive secondary will need some work, he does return 
all-league defensive end Heaton and linebacker Vasquez, who plan to vex 
opponents and cause general mayhem. Overall, Turek said the team is fired up 
and can't wait for the season to begin. "They really want Rancho (Alamitos) 
again," Turek said. "They knocked us out in the first round (of playoffs) and 
you can understand we would like another shot at them." In comparison to other 
Freeway League teams, Troy has some good depth with 21 returning lettermen and 
nine starters from last year. And whether or not senior Kevin Gray will be able 
to fill the gap left by All-League quarterback Brian Logan, it is still too 
early to see if the 6 foot-1 Gray can pull it off. 
</P>
