all-league quarterback Cabral, who helped get Buena Park get to the playoffs 
last season. The senior is hoping to return to play in October. Until then, the 
Coyotes will have to rely on Hudson, who also plays defensive back. 
Additionally, Ray, the tight end/linebacker who was an all-league second-team 
selection as a sophomore, is coming off an injury that kept him out of the 
entire 1993 season. But Buena Park and Rau seem to be able to make things 
happen, and there's still Jones, an all-league running back. With the 
graduation of Wali Sibrie, the 6-foot-3, 270-pound offensive lineman who is now 
at Arizona State, the Coyotes are definitely not a huge team. Only one starter 
weighs more than 200 pounds. But what they don't have in size, they make up for 
in quickness. But factors like whether Ray can duplicate his '92 season and 
when Cabral returns might be the difference between a winning and losing 
campaign. 
