<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: JONES TO COACH BOYS' TRACK AT QUARTZ HILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Casey Jones, girls' track coach at Quartz Hill High since 1989, has been named 
head coach of the Rebels' boys' program. 
</P>
<P>
 Jones, a 1976 graduate of Quartz Hill, replaces Don Crimin, who stepped down 
as boys' coach in June. 
</P>
<P>
 Crimin has been involved with Quartz Hill athletics since the school opened in 
1964 and is expected to return as a volunteer assistant. 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Moeller, an assistant football and track coach at Littlerock High for the 
past two years, will replace Jones as girls' coach. 
</P>
<P>
 The Quartz Hill girls' team has won six consecutive Golden League track 
titles. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Jon Bischop, who finished ninth in the 3,200 meters in this year's Southern 
Section Division I championships for Canyon High, will attend Southern 
California College in Costa Mesa. Soccer 
</P>
<P>
 Tami Pivnick of Chaminade High scored two goals in the championship game of 
the Maccabiah Games as Los Angeles won the gold medal with a 4-1 victory over 
New York. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles (5-0) scored 15 goals and allowed only three during the 
tournament. 
</P>
