LOCAL NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cal State Fullerton men's soccer team, which begins its season Saturday, 
is ranked fourth nationally in a poll released this week. 
</P>
<P>
 The Titans received 375 points in the Intercollegiate Soccer Assn. of America 
preseason poll, which ranks Virginia No. 1 with 478 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton opens its season Saturday at home against Sacramento State in the 
Reebok Classic at 7:30 p.m. Last season, Fullerton was 16-7, 5-2 in the Pacific 
Division of the Mountain Pacific Soccer Federation. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Delphia Moore, a former Orange High hurdler, has signed an letter of intent to 
attend Cal State Northridge on a track scholarship, Orange Coach Lanny Carter 
said. Moore was the Century League champion in the 300 intermediate hurdles 
last spring, and her top mark of 43.6 seconds was second-best in Orange County. 
 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Nate Morton, a junior center, transferred from Ocean View High to Calvary 
Chapel, a Calvary Chapel school administrator confirmed Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Morton, 6 feet 5, enrolled at Calvary Chapel in early August, Athletic 
Director Kris Van Hook said. Morton should be a big addition for the Eagles 
(12-13, 6-5 in Olympic League play), who have several players returning. 
</P>
