<HEADLINE>
<P>
41 TO BE CHARGED IN QUEBEC DRUG STING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Forty-one people arrested in a Quebec sting operation will be charged with 
laundering more than $73 million in drug money, police said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Royal Canadian Mounted Police said the arrests capped a four-year 
undercover operation in Quebec, other Canadian provinces and abroad. In 
addition to money-laundering charges, 26 people face charges of conspiracy for 
cocaine trafficking and 12 will be charged with importing and distributing 
hashish from Jamaica. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA083194-0142 </DOCNO>
