METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; COAST 
GUARD TO STEP UP CHECKS FOR DRUNK BOATERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Coast Guard plans to step up enforcement along the entire California coast 
this Labor Day weekend, which traditionally is one of the busiest boating 
weekends of the year. 
</P>
<P>
 The idea is to get boaters who have had too much to drink off the water, a 
spokesman said. Accidents involving alcohol and boating have been on the rise 
in California, according to Coast Guard spokesman Dennis Hall. 
</P>
<P>
 Coast Guard crews will stop boats and administer sobriety tests to occupants 
if the pilot of a vessel appears intoxicated.LABOR DAY 
</P>
