<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; RAP STAR 
GETS 5 MONTHS IN DRUNK DRIVING CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rap star Dr. Dre was sentenced Tuesday in Los Angeles Municipal Court to five 
months in jail after pleading no contest to drunk driving charges. 
</P>
<P>
 The 28-year-old Grammy-winning rapper, whose real name is Andre Young, will 
enter jail on Jan. 10 under a work furlough arrangement allowing him to leave 
his cell on a daily basis to continue producing records in his home studio in 
Calabasas. 
</P>
<P>
 Police arrested Young on Jan. 10 after he failed a sobriety test after an 
earlymorning high-speed chase through Beverly Hills and Westwood. In addition 
to the five-month jail term, West Los Angeles Municipal Judge Paula Adela 
Mabrey also ordered the entertainer to pay a $1,053 fine and attend an alcohol 
education program. 
</P>
<P>
 The judge ruled that Young had violated the terms of a three-year probated 
sentence stemming from a 1992 battery conviction in which he allegedly punched 
a Woodland Hills man in the face, breaking his jaw. 
</P>
</TEXT>
