<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; MAYOR AND 
COUNCIL HONOR NORTHRIDGE LITTLE LEAGUERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The "Earthquake Kids," who captured the U.S. title at the Little League World 
Series, were honored Tuesday by Mayor Richard Riordan and the Los Angeles City 
Council. 
</P>
<P>
 Riordan and Councilman Hal Bernson, whose district includes Northridge, passed 
out honorary resolutions to each of the team's coaches and players. About 100 
people in the council chamber applauded as Coach Larry Baca introduced the 
youngsters. 
</P>
<P>
 Riordan, Bernson and other council members lauded the team as a symbol of the 
city's recovery from the Jan. 17 quake.  
</P>
<P>
 About 70% of the team members had to leave their homes after the quake, and 
three were still living elsewhere as the team headed to Williamsport, Pa., for 
the playoffs. 
</P>
