</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A representative from City Councilwoman Laura Chick's office will be on hand 
today to discuss crime and other concerns with west Van Nuys merchants at a 
meeting of the Corporate/Business Watch. 
</P>
<P>
 The 6 p.m. meeting at American Pacific State Bank, 16600 Sherman Way, will 
feature Rayna Gabin, a field deputy from Chick's San Fernando Valley office. 
</P>
<P>
 "The meeting will be to discuss how the City Council can get more involved 
with the Los Angeles Police Department and the Corporate/Business Watch," said 
Shelly Joanis, who organized the watch program. 
</P>
<P>
