OFF THE TICKER: PINBALL STILL FILLING THE ARCADES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AMY HARMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pinball, it seems, is still profitable. 
</P>
<P>
 At a time when "Super Streetfighter 2" and sophisticated virtual reality games 
are all the rage at the video arcade, Sega Enterprises Ltd. plans to acquire 
Chicago-based Data East Pinball, the world's second-largest pinball maker. 
</P>
<P>
 Terms of the deal were not disclosed, but Sega, the $4-billion Japanese video 
game giant that has built a reputation as a cutting-edge interactive 
entertainment firm, said in a news release that pinball machines "continue to 
be a dominant element in the amusement arcade industry." AMY HARMON 
</P>
