<P>
 Study of Cellular Phone Risks Revised: Cellular telephone users may be exposed 
to greater levels of potentially dangerous electromagnetic energy than 
previously thought, according to revised figures from Om Ghandi, a researcher 
at the University of Utah.He recalculated data from an earlier study of 10 
cellular phones and found higher levels of electromagnetic energy than were 
originally reported. Lawsuits have alleged a connection between cellular phone 
use and some forms of brain cancer. A spokesman for the Washington-based 
Cellular Telecommunications Industry Assn. said that, even using the revised 
data, the amount of electromagnetic energy emitted falls within established 
safety guidelines. 
