<P>
 American Airlines to Reduce Headquarters Staff: The nation's largest carrier 
in terms of revenue said it will reduce its headquarters staff as part of a 
program to lower costs. The job cuts, which have yet to be determined, will be 
another step in the airline's campaign to save $750 million in annual labor 
costs and become more competitive with low-fare challengers such as Southwest 
Airlines Co.American, a unit of AMR Corp., said it is looking to save an 
additional $250 million a year in other parts of its operations. About 10,000 
of American's 90,000 employees work at the headquarters near the Dallas-Ft. 
Worth airport. A study over the next five months, conducted by an outside 
consultant, will determine the extent of the cuts, American said. 
