<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saba Petroleum Co.: The small independent oil producer is moving to increase 
its presence in Oklahoma. 
</P>
<P>
 The Irvine-based company announced Tuesday that it is purchasing several oil 
wells and gas properties for $11 million. Company spokesman Husai Rokerya would 
not identify the seller. The properties Saba has agreed to purchase are now 
producing 800 barrels of crude oil a day and 750 million cubic feet of natural 
gas daily, the company said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
