<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: CANON INTRODUCES COLOR PRINTER; WATSON MAKES OIL DEAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Canon Computer Systems Inc. said Tuesday it has introduced a color printer for 
personal computers that will sell for about $500. 
</P>
<P>
 The printer uses tiny jets of yellow, blue, magenta and black ink to make 
images on standard copier paper, film and sheets of other material. 
</P>
<P>
 Canon officials said they hope the new product will help them increase their 
share of the printer market, now led by Hewlett-Packard Co. 
</P>
</TEXT>
