<HEADLINE>
<P>
ABT ANNOUNCES 'MANON' CASTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ZAN DUBIN, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cynthia Harvey will dance the title role in American Ballet Theatre's 
production of "Manon" on Sept. 20, the opening night of the troupe's six-day 
run at the Orange County Performing Arts Center.  
</P>
<P>
 Guillaume Graffin will appear opposite Harvey, and Gil Boggs and Kathleen 
Moore will handle supporting roles in Kenneth MacMillan's ballet.It will be the 
first time ABT has danced the full-length "Manon" in Southern California. 
</P>
<P>
 In subsequent performances, the leads will be Julie Kent and Robert Hill, 
Susan Jaffe and Charles Askegard and Harvey and Graffin. Each pair will dance 
"Manon" twice. 
</P>
<P>
 ABT gives the first West Coast performances of James Kudelka's "Cruel World" 
on two mixed repertory programs that also include Natalia Makarova's staging of 
"The Kingdom of the Shades" from "La Bayadere" and Twyla Tharp's "In the Upper 
Room." 
</P>
<P>
 Casting, subject to change: 
</P>
<P>
 * Tuesday, Sept. 20, 8 p.m.: "Manon," Cynthia Harvey, Guillaume Graffin, Gill 
Boggs, Kathleen Moore. 
</P>
<P>
 * Wednesday, Sept. 21, 8 p.m.: "La Bayadere," Susan Jaffe, Parrish Maynard. 
"Cruel World" and "In the Upper Room," ensemble pieces. 
</P>
<P>
 * Thursday, Sept. 22, 8 p.m.: "La Bayadere," Harvey, Graffin. "Cruel World" 
and "In the Upper Room," ensemble pieces. 
</P>
<P>
 * Friday, Sept. 23, 8 p.m.: "Manon," Julie Kent, Robert Hill, Keith Roberts, 
Christina Fagundes. 
</P>
<P>
 * Saturday, Sept. 24, 2 p.m.: "Manon," Jaffe, Charles Askegard, Ethan Brown, 
Kathleen Moore. 
</P>
<P>
 * Saturday, Sept. 24, 8 p.m.: "Manon," Harvey, Graffin, Boggs, Moore. 
</P>
<P>
 * Sunday, Sept. 25, 2 p.m.: "Manon," Kent, Hill, Roberts, Fagundes. 
</P>
<P>
 * Sunday, Sept. 25, 8 p.m.: "Manon," Jaffe, Askegard, Brown, Christine Dunham. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets, $18 to $55, are available through Ticketmaster, (714) 740-2000 or 
(213) 480-3232, or at the center, 600 Town Center Drive, Costa Mesa, (714) 
556-2787.ORANGE COUNTY PERFORMING ARTS CENT 
</P>
</TEXT>
